The paper discusses the development of an open source, user-friendly AI system specialized for machine learning analysis of complex data in the biomedical and health care domains. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of genetic programming to aid in the development of the AI system, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The focus on biomedical and health care data suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.CE (Computational Biology and Bioinformatics) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) sub-categories. Finally, the paper may also belong to the cs.DB (Databases) sub-category, as it discusses the need for accessible AI systems for individual researchers and the general public.
